      "SummaryText": "es ensure rigorous training for operations employees, an effective mechanical integrity program, numerous management checks and balances, and strict attention to changes in the operations with a thorough review and examination of potential incidents that could lead to an accidental release.\n\nBostik maintains a 24-hour corporate emergency reporting system that can speedily coordinates emergency response with management and quickly communicate key first-aid or medical information to local health care providers. This facility has emergency medical treatment information readily available for use in the event of an emergency.\n\nThe five-year accident history [40 CFR 68.155(d)]:\n\nDuring the past five years, we have not had any releases of the regulated substances that have resulted in or could have resulted in an offsite impact.\n\nThe emergency response program [40 CFR 68.155(e)]:\n\nEmployees at our facility are Defensive Responders. Emergency Response releases (as defined in 29CFR1910.120) requiring offensive actions are handled by outside emergency response teams. Site employees are trained and instructed to implement defensive actions only. This facility invites local fire departments and emergency responders to tour and inspect the plant, and gain familiarity with our operations. This facility also has a written emergency preparedness plan that is updated regularly. The facility currently has five fixed foam systems for fire control and vapor mitigation. In addition, the facility has three fixed water deluge systems. \n\nPlanned changes to improve safety [40 CFR 68.155(f)]:\n\nOur facility continually evaluates and implements employee suggestions and recommendations resulting from process hazard analyses. We make changes to improve reliability and safety based on information developed within our organization and industry. Toward continuous improvement, we are looking at ways to minimize risk through process improvement, process re-design, and formulation substitution."
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000112564,
      "SummaryText": "The accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the stationary source [40 CFR 68.155(a)]:\n\nBostik Inc. relies on numerous policies and programs to ensure employee, public, and environmental safety including early identification of and proper response to potential emergencies, such as:\n\n-  Training  in emergency preparedness, hazardous materials training, disaster response and control, first-aid, and fire-and-rescue techniques;\n-  Frequent auditing of all preparedness programs; safety training and education; and\n-  Regular review, follow-up, and maintenance of all company operations and equipment.\n\nOur facilities regularly invite local fire departments and emergency responders to tour and inspect our plants to gain familiarity with our operations. Our facilities have written emergency preparedness plans that are reviewed updated regularly.\n\nBostik makes an effort to support our communities through sponsorship of local activities and participation in local organizations.\n\nThe stationary source and regulated substances handled [40 CFR 68.155(b)]:\n\nBostik's Calumet City facility manufactures a variety of acrylic and phenolic resins for the Specialty Polymers and Adhesives industry. Fifty weight percent formaldehyde (formalin) and vinyl acetate monomer are the two substances present which are regulated under the USEPA Risk Management Program Rule, 40 CFR 68. There are no RMP-regulated flammables on site meeting the RMP threshold quantity.\n\nFor more information, visit our web site at www.ashspec.com or contact the Plant Manager.\n\nThe general accidental release prevention program and chemical-specific prevention steps [40 CFR 68.155(c)]:\n\nThis facility is operated in strict accordance with the USEPA prevention program requirements. The program includes process safety information, hazard reviews, and a management of change process. A written management system is in place with operating and maintenance procedures